Canal Albert
(10-12 May 1940)

General, the expected German attack has started. Early in the morning the Germans have crossed the Dutch border and in few hours they will arrive at our "Position de Couverture"  situated behind the Canal Albert. With the support of the strong fortress of Eben-Emael, you must contain the Germans in the "Position de couverture" for as long as possible in order to allow our troops, as well as that of our French and British allies, to occupy their positions in the "Ligne KW", the main defence line where is foreseen to fight the decisive battle. It is essential therefore that the Germans do not take the bridges of the Canal Albert.

If the situation requires so, some reinforcements of the Corps de Cavalerie may be put at your disposition. 

Victory condiotions: keep 7 VH for a BV, 4 VH for a V and 2 VH for a TV.

Tip: blow the bridges before the Germans capture them

Map: Canal Albert (828)

Paqueo, December 2010
